main event: On September 5, 1956, three unidentified flying objects were observed in Concord, New Hampshire.
interesting points: The observation was classified as both ground and air visual., The objects were reported to be moving upward and fast., Initial conclusions suggested the possibility of a balloon, though there was insufficient data to confirm this., The sighting lasted approximately 25 seconds with a range of 6 miles., There is no photograph available associated with this sighting.
